# Obsidian open

Invokes a wrapper script that launches `obsidian://open?vault={{VAULT_NAME}}&file=<encoded>`. The vault is registered with Obsidian as `{{VAULT_NAME}}`.

## Path convention
Obsidian URI takes **vault-relative** paths. From repo root, strip the leading `{{VAULT_DIR}}/`:

| Repo path | Obsidian-relative path |
| --- | --- |
| `{{VAULT_DIR}}/wiki/entities/Example.md` | `wiki/entities/Example.md` |
| `{{VAULT_DIR}}/wiki/sources/example-source.md` | `wiki/sources/example-source.md` |
| `{{VAULT_DIR}}/raw/sources/example.md` | `raw/sources/example.md` |

## Git Bash / Linux / macOS
```bash
./{{SCRIPTS_DIR}}/obsidian-open.sh wiki/entities/Example.md
```

## PowerShell
```powershell
powershell -File {{SCRIPTS_DIR}}/obsidian-open.ps1 -Path "wiki/entities/Example.md"
```

## When to use
- Just finished writing or editing a wiki page
- User said "open X" or "show me X in Obsidian"
- After an ingest pass, open the new source page for the user to inspect

## When NOT to use
- Bulk operations — opening many files spams Obsidian's tab bar
- Read-only query flows — just cite the path

## Setup (one-time, user action)
1. Launch Obsidian → "Open folder as vault" → select the `{{VAULT_DIR}}/` folder.
2. Name the vault **{{VAULT_NAME}}** when prompted.
3. Settings → Community plugins → disable restricted mode → enable `Dataview` and `Marp`.

## Notes
- Paths are URL-encoded by the wrapper so spaces and unicode work.
- If Obsidian isn't running, the OS will launch it first, then open the file.
